    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1866-12-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1866-12-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="391" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d391">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Coggeshall</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 12.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1866-12-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 5, 1866</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatches Nos. 13 and 14 have been
                            received. In your No. 14 you gave me an account of the agitation in
                            diplomatic circles of complaints of the United States of Colombia
                            against Ecuador.</p>
                <p>You inform me that speculations concerning a movement for the free
                            navigation of the Amazon are connected with those rumors. I shall hold
                            myself under obligation for such other information as you can give me on
                            that interesting subject.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. T. Coggeshall,</hi> Esq., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., <hi rend="italic">Quito.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
